text: :There are also other places called Dromore Dromore (Droim MÃ³r, meaning "Big Ridge", in Irish) is a village in County Tyrone, Northern Ireland. It is nine miles (15 km) southwest of Omagh on the A32 road and sixteen miles (26 km) from Enniskillen. The village had a population of 1,101 in 2001. Agriculture and the building trades are the primary sources of employment in the town. It is in the Omagh District Council area. == Other websites == *Dromore Community website Category:Villages in Northern Ireland
